args:
Just as Cleo and Mitsuba feed Pecorine a
restoring rice porridge, Aether attacks once
more. In this moment of crisis, the power of
bonds comes through the food and allows her
to make a complete recovery. The three of them
then challenge Aether to a final battle.
That means it's healthy and chock-full\nof tasty nutrients. Let's take it down!
Oh, what's taking them so long?
Your compatriots are back, miss—\nthough I fear they are covered in blood.

I'm sorry, I should have been more clear.
It is not THEIR blood; rather, it comes from
the fiend they slayed and brought here.
I do hope they don't stain my floors...
Sorry to barge in on you,\nbut we need the kitchen, stat!
No problem, dear. All guests are allowed\nto cook their own food here.
Mitsuba, you're on rice duty.\nI'll prep the fiendmeat.
Oh, we're better than all right—\njust look at all this meat!
Do you want to help us cook?
The three work diligently in the kitchen, until...
And there we have it... Fiendmeat\nmiso porridge, packed full of all the\nmedicinal herbs a girl could need!
I can't believe how good it smells...
Let us feed it to Pecorine at once!
Eating while sleeping, huh?\nThat sounds like our girl, all right.
The mana flowing through her body\nis springing to life...
If she keeps eating the porridge,\nher strength is bound to return!
Uh oh. Was that a scream?\nIt came from the town square.
We should go and see. Lumière Pandora,\nplease keep feeding her the porridge.
A rift to another world? Oh no...
TARGET THREAT-LEVEL UPDATED.\nSELECTING OPTIMAL FORM FOR\nELIMINATION.
Oh dear. Things sound dire out there.\nI do hope everyone is all right.
Come on, Pecorine. You need to keep\neating so you can wake up.
It's like really soft rice...\nRice porridge, maybe?
But we've also got some meat going on,\nas well as herbs and a touch of miso.\nWhat a combination!
The rice reminds me of the kind I used\nto eat with the Gourmet Guild.
The meat and miso are familiar, too. \nWhere have I had this before...?
Wait, this isn't just meat—it's fiendmeat!\nWhich means it must have been made by...
...Yep! That's it, all right!\nI feel it in every bite.
They put so much love into this dish.
Guess I'll have to repay the favor!
And I know just how to do it...
INCONCEIVABLE. ATTACK PATTERNS\nHAVE DIVERGED FROM THE LAST BATTLE.
ACCORDING TO ANALYSIS, HUMANS ARE\nAN IRRATIONAL LIFE-FORM CONTROLLED\nBY THEIR FEELINGS.
Yeah, even now, it hurts to fight something\nthat looks like my friends.
But when we froze up last time,\nit led to our other friend getting hurt.
So we won't let that happen again.\nWe'll defeat you no matter what!
ANALYSIS FAILED. THOUGHT PATTERNS\nHAVE LED TO UNFORESEEN ACTIONS.\nSTRATEGY ADAPTATION COMMENCING.
It's taken that giant form again!
That huge thing is coming right for us!
It's targeting the villagers in order to\nplace us on the defensive!
Talk about your cowardly moves...\nBut we still can't let up!
That's right! Thanks to your rice porridge,\nI've made a full recovery.
I'm so touched you'd make something\nlike that for me.
We would do anything for a friend.
Whoops! No time to get mushy, I guess.\nLumière, you help the villagers escape.
Now then, how do we wanna cook up\nthis humongous Aether?
The rift it came out of is right behind it.
To limit damage to the village,\nwe should first push it back inside.
Sounds like a plan. Here we go!
You're in hot water now, beast!
I'm going all out! Time to slice and dice!\nPrincess Strike!
Into the rift, everyone; it's time to\nend this madness once and for all!
Right! This is our final battle!
